The paper deals with recommendation systems for Location-Based Social Networks (LBSNs), which involves analyzing user behavior and preferences in a social and geographical context. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SI, cs.IR), as well as Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multiple network embeddings, which could also relate to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC).
